      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:4:3:223:6",
      "text": [
        " سَمِعْتُ أَبَا عَبْدِ اللَّهِ ( عليه السلام ) يَقُولُ قَالَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ( صلى الله عليه وآله ) مَنْ أَحْدَثَ بِالْمَدِينَةِ حَدَثاً أَوْ آوَى مُحْدِثاً فَعَلَيْهِ لَعْنَةُ اللَّهِ قُلْتُ وَ مَا الْحَدَثُ قَالَ الْقَتْلُ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, and Muhammad Bin Ismail, from Al Fazl Bin Shazaan, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Jameel Bin Darraj who said, ",
          "‘I heard Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> saying: ‘Rasool-Allah<sup>saww</sup> said: ‘Whoever causes an incident in Al-Medina or shelters an incident maker, so upon him is the Curse of Allah<sup>azwj</sup>’. I said, ‘And what is the incident?’ He<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘The killing’."
        ]
      }
    },
